    isd.imm-dr4
------------------------------------------------------------

What?

    This is a thing to draw using DR4 like a normal
    drawing library. Without long-living objects.

How?

    We have a single static object for each type.

What if window closes? How objects are allocated?

    We also have WinRef, which is added as a field
    to each object which lives inside the window.
    (like widgets). When first WinRef for given 
    window is created, objects are allocated.
    When last is destroyed, objects are destroyed.

What is contained withn plugin?

    Plugin has only one purpose -- make so that instance
    is one for all the program. Singleton, as someone
    would say.
